 will cover multiple fundage situations, going in ascending order.<br>
<br>
<br>
1) dirt poor (1k or less)<br>
<br>
  Go for weapons first, IMO. Get a shaded weapon, a jarsath trident...anything with a good ratio and no lvl req that is cheap. Pick up something else when you get lvl 13 for dual wield, you could have more money then. 2handers are also good, you can pick up a BABS (24/39 or something) for like 50pp on Povar. After that, go for jewelry. 6/65 rings, or, if you have less left, adm bands till you can afford upgrades. Remember, hp is GREAT for twinks. Any leftover should be spent on getting a few armor pieces (crafted, ry'gorr, validus custodus, crusty... these are all dirt cheap now)<br>
<br>
2) medium funds (2-5k)<br>
<br>
  Again, start with weapons. Don't go extravagant, get something like jmace/centi, something with good ratios and not too expensive, working 2 skills is also good to cut prices on skill-up weapons. Jewelry, go on and pick up 6/65 rings and BSE (2ac 35hp) ears, they'll last ya forever. If ya got the money, pick up FBSS or SCHW for haste. If not, go on and fill out the armor with crafted, crusty, validus custodus, ry'gorr, anything that has comparable stats. Don't have to go for the cheapest now. Pick up a glimmering mithril torque for the neck, tattered mantle for the shoulders, and (if they're cheap on your server) crystal spider eyes for the face. As you get more money, look to get haste if you don't have it, better weapons, and then thurg MQs/cobalt.<br>
<br>
 3) 10kish funds<br>
  Start with weapons, once again. Get a nice one this time. Seb dirk, crafted velium warsword, frosty.... depending on server prices. look to spend about 5k on both weapons. Get 6/65s and 2ac 35hp ears again, as well as the same neck/shoulder/face. Get FBSS/SCHW, pick up some nice armor (acrylia plate, cobalt, barbed ringmail... just look for deals on nice stuff) Fill in spare slots with afforementioned filler armor.<br>
<br>
 4) 20kish<br>
<br>
 Get nice weapons. seb dirk, frosty, CBoL... I'd spend 10k on both weapons. Pick up FBSS/SCHW, again. Get the same jewelry, face/shoulders/neck, and look for the acrylia plate/barbed ringmail/cobalt... just get more of it. Acrylia plate is cheap and quite nice, I'd suggest quite a few pieces of the stuff. As soon as you can get faction Thurg MQs are nice too.<br>
<br>
 5) lots of money (50-100k)<br>
<br>
 Get fungi if you can afford it. It is the best twink item, period. After that, use the cash to buy weapons such as the ones mentioned above, fierce heraldic/cobalt/thurg MQs, haste item, same jewelry mentioned above, deathmask of the elysians, gantru warmask, clattering bone necklace... look for hp/sta as well as ac. Fill in remaining slots with items metioned above.<br>
<br>
 There it is, my twink guide. This is done by Povar prices, and shopping around a bit, could be different on your server. I will finish up with my own personal twink, If I could get anything I wanted for a lvl 1 warrior.<br>
<br>
 weapons: SBoZ, HoH (i'd say BoC, but it's completely unrealistic)<br>
 Chest: fungi<br>
 Legs: cobalt<br>
 Arms: Fierce heraldic (sure sure, the lvl req, but with this stuff you'll be 45 in like a day anyways)<br>
 earrings: iron cog (unless it has lvl req?) mosquito leg<br>
 rings: djarns, 6/65<br>
 face: deathmask of the elysians<br>
 shoulders: the 65hp, sta ones that are chokidai or sarnak or something... you figure it out.<br>
 Head: cowl of mortality<br>
 feet: boots of the storm<br>
 bracers: fierce heraldic, crystallized acid<br>
 gaunts: fierce heraldic, something i could find high Hp<br>
 necklace: clattering bone<br>
 range: idol of the thorned<br>
 <br>
 If I left out any slots, oh well. hope this helps some folks, going to play EQ now.<br>
